The paper proposes a modified knowledge distillation procedure to obtain computationally-efficient uncertainty estimates with deep networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The proposed method is evaluated on image classification tasks, indicating that computer vision (cs.CV) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks (cs.NE) and deep learning (cs.DL), further supporting these sub-categories.
